If you want Twisted-Web running under Apache's mod_proxy or a similar
reverse proxy configuration, take the following steps:

cp /usr/share/doc/twisted-web/examples/02vhostmonster.py \
   /etc/twisted-web/local.d

Edit /etc/twisted-web/twisted-web, and change the port "80" to something else

Put in Apache's config something like:

=========
<VirtualHost ip-addr>
ProxyPass / http://localhost:8538/vhost/http/example.com:80/
ServerName example.com
</VirtualHost>
==========
